wikipedia_page.main: Ashlee Ageron Jones (born 4 August 1987) is an English footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for Waltham Abbey. Jones came through the ranks at Southampton where he was a member of the squad that reached the FA Youth Cup Final in 2005. He later played in the Football League for Darlington, and includes Rushden & Diamonds, Wycombe Wanderers, Braintree Town and Lowestoft Town among his former clubs.
